      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It makes sense that your energy feels futile when the world is collapsing, and that hollow feeling is a very real and valid response to such despair. You don't have to pretend that building your life matters if the foundation is gone; sometimes, the only true act of resistance is to make your own existence intentional, even if it feels temporary. But consider that your presence and your choices in this moment still create ripples that might help others survive the crash, even if you can't stop the fire itself.",
      "source": "target",
